2\int_0^{2\pi} \left|\cos\left(\frac{\theta}{2}\right)\right|d\theta
4\int_0^{\pi} \cos\left(\frac{\theta}{2}\right)d\theta
\displaystyle f_1 (x) = \cos \frac{x}{2}
\displaystyle f_2 (x) = |f_1 (x)|
f_2 (x)
x = \pi
\displaystyle |\cos \frac{\theta}{2}|
2 \int_0^{2\pi} |\cos \frac{\theta}{2}| d\theta = 2 \int_0^{\pi} \cos \frac{\theta}{2} d\theta + 2 \int_{\pi}^{2\pi} \cos \left(\pi - \frac{\theta}{2}\right) d\theta = 4 \int_0^{\pi} \cos \frac{\theta}{2} d\theta
